Three teams, Inter Milan, Bayern Munich and Real Madrid will come together to launch the ‘European Solidarity Cup’ set for 2021 in a bid to raise funds to back medical infrastructures due to the coronavirus pandemic. The ‘European Solidarity Cup will see the trio of teams play against each other and matches will be played in each city – Milan (Inter vs FC Bayern), Madrid (Real vs Inter), and Munich (Bayern vs Real Madrid). However, no dates have been confirmed for the abovementioned but the clubs have released statements confirming the matches and what they hope to achieve thereafter.